member.example:

long x,y,d;
d = Fn.GreatestCommonDivisor(45,18,out x, out y);
-> d == 9 && x == 1 && y == -2

The gcd of 45 and 18 is 9: 18 = 2*9, 45 = 5*9. 9 = 1*45 -2*18, therefore x=1 and y=-2.

para.code:
Complex x = Complex.FromRealImaginary(1d, 2d);
Complex y = Complex.FromModulusArgument(1d, Math.Pi);
Complex z = (x + y) / (x - y);

member.remarks:
The semantic of setting the conjugate is such that

// a, b of type Complex
a.Conjugate = b;

is equivalent to

// a, b of type Complex
a = b.Conjugate

para.code:
Complex32 x = Complex32.FromRealImaginary(1d, 2d);
Complex32 y = Complex32.FromModulusArgument(1d, Math.Pi);
Complex32 z = (x + y) / (x - y);

member.remarks:
The semantic of setting the conjugate is such that

// a, b of type Complex32
a.Conjugate = b;

is equivalent to

// a, b of type Complex32
a = b.Conjugate
